<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">REQ #</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">Description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">REQ01</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Only one task can be selected per scheduled task=
, but it is not required</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">REQ02</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">Scheduled tasks are stored per user, they can't =
be shared (TBD Security)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">REQ03</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Each of the creation tabpages have=
 validation and one can not progress to the next tabpage before the validat=
ion succeeds. The validation messages are written as clear as possible and =
displayed as an error notification. See <a href=3D"/wiki/spaces/RASNEX/page=
s/83755292/3.2+RAS+UI%3A+Input+Validation" data-linked-resource-id=3D"83755=
292" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"page">=
3.2 RAS UI: Input Validation</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">REQ04</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">On tab 1. Schedule a valid schedul=
e should be selected by default so no validation necessary</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">REQ05</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">On tab 2. Task only one task has t=
o be selected</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">REQ06</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>On tab 3. Messaging when email =
is ticked:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>a valid 'TO:' recipient should be present</li>
<li>a valid Subject should be present</li>
<li>a non empty message body should be present</li>
</ul><p>when website notification is ticked</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>a valid 'TO:' RAS user should be present</li>
<li>a non empty message body should be present</li>
<li>the maximum length of the notification should be 300 characters</li>
<li>the only allowed html tag is an &lt;a href&gt;</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">REQ07</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">On tab 4. Complete scheduled task =
a title is required</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">REQ08</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">When selecting a website notificat=
ion as the message format, the user can only select ras users which are a m=
ember of the company the user is in. It should be possible to select the us=
ers from a list using autocomplete functionality</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">REQ09</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Each message should have a foot=
er with the following information:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>The owner of the task that generated the message</li>
<li>The task that generated the message</li>
<li>The moment of generation</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">REQ10</td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">For each type of task, internally,=
 we should define a default template for the subject as well as the body of=
 the email</td>
</tr>
